Consumer and business confidence in the U.S. economy is on the rise, with Americans rating the economy as good to excellent at its highest level in 18 years. Concerns about healthcare are high, while worries about energy and unemployment are low. Business economists are optimistic about economic growth in 2018, projecting a 2.9 percent expansion. U.S. consumer confidence has reached a 14-year high, with lower-income households feeling more optimistic. The majority of companies plan to enhance compensation due to the new GOP tax reform law. Job openings in the U.S. have surged to a record high, indicating strong labor demand. The number of Americans collecting unemployment benefits and relying on food stamps has dropped to the lowest levels in decades.